HEADWORD: Clothespin
<hw>Clothes"pin`</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A forked
piece of wood or plastic, or a small device with a spring clamp, used
for fastening clothes on a line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

